SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The coronary sinus/left ventricular lead was not implanted because the operator was unable to obtain acceptable pacing thresholds.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: COULD NOT OBTAIN ACCEPTABLE PACING THRESHOLDS
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Unable to Obtain Acceptable Pacing Thresholds

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The coronary sinus/left ventricular lead was not implanted because the lead position resulted in undesirable stimulation of the diaphragm.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: LEAD POSITION RESULTS IN UNDESIRABLE STIMULATION OF THE DIAPHRAGM
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Cardiac Lead Position Results in Undesirable Stimulation of Diaphragm

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The coronary sinus/left ventricular lead was not implanted because a lead had been previously implanted.
The coronary sinus/left ventricular lead was not implanted because the operator was unable to obtain satisfactory coronary sinus access.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: UNABLE TO OBTAIN SATISFACTORY CORONARY SINUS ACCESS
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Unable to Obtain Satisfactory Coronary Sinus Access

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The coronary sinus/left ventricular lead was not implanted because the operator was unable to obtain satisfactory vascular access.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: UNABLE TO OBTAIN SATISFACTORY VASCULAR ACCESS
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Unable to Obtain Satisfactory Vascular Access

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The coronary sinus/left ventricular lead was not implanted because the coronary sinus was dissected.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: UNABLE TO POSITION LEAD DUE TO CORONARY SINUS DISSECTION
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Unable to Position Lead Due to Coronary Sinus Dissection

SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: The coronary sinus/left ventricular lead was not implanted because the operator was unable to position the lead in the tributary vein of the coronary sinus.
SKOS_CONCEPT.notation: UNABLE TO POSITION LEAD IN TRIBUTARY VEIN OF CORONARY SINUS
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Unable to Position Lead In tributary Vein of Coronary Sinus
